          <heading>Action upon investigation</heading>
          <content>
            <p>§346-228
Action upon investigation.
Upon investigation the department shall take action to prevent abuse and
shall have the authority to do any or all of the following:
(1)  Resolve the matter in an informal fashion as is
appropriate under the circumstances;
(2)  Exercise its right of entry under section
346-229;
(3)  Seek an order for immediate protection;
(4)  Seek a temporary restraining order;
(5)  File a petition with the court under this part;
and
(6)  Seek any protective or remedial actions
authorized by law. [L 1989, c 381, pt of §1; am L 1990, c 144, §1 and c 234,
§9; am L 2008, c 154, §10]
